hopobject.body: Where are you calling from? isotretinoin gel sebaceous hyperplasia But before you gather all your willpower and attempt to boycott Facebook, you should consider whether giving up the social network will really make you happier. This most recent study is hardly full-proof. For one, the sample size of 82 participants is pretty tiny. And the researchers admit that the statistically significant associations between Facebook usage and well-being are "'relatively' small." They also note that the way the data was collected "can obscure interesting differences."
